From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] drm: sunxi: fix init_connecting fallback to probe all connectors

init_connecting() has a fallback path for when the bootloader didn't
set up a display (init_cnt == 0).  The fallback only probes connectors[0]
and, if that connector has no modes, starts hot-plug monitoring on it and
returns with connecting_head empty.

On the Cubie A7S, connectors[0] is HDMI-A-1 (disconnected at boot), and
connectors[1] is DP-1 (a USB-C DP AltMode display that IS connected).
The EDP driver's bind code already runs AUX communication successfully
and sets hpd_state=true before init_connecting() runs, so DP-1 would
return modes if fill_modes() were called on it.  But it never is.

Result: connecting_head stays empty → commit_init_connecting() is a
no-op → the display hardware pipeline (TCON4 + DE + EDP PHY) is never
properly initialized at kernel level → blank screen, even though the
USB-C DP AltMode negotiation succeeded and EDID was read correctly.

Fix: replace the single-connector fallback with a two-pass loop:
  pass 0 — probe non-HDMI connectors first (DP, eDP)
  pass 1 — probe HDMI connectors if nothing was found in pass 0

For each connector that returns modes, find the correct CRTC by
inspecting the connector's encoder(s) and their possible_crtcs bitmask.
This avoids using crtcs[0] for a connector that actually needs crtcs[N].

If no connector has modes (genuine cold-boot with nothing connected),
fall back to hot-plug monitoring on the first detect-capable connector,
same as before.

Signed-off-by: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
---
 bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c | 63 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 52 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c b/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c
--- a/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c
+++ b/bsp/drivers/drm/sunxi_drm_drv.c
@@ -941,28 +941,69 @@ static int init_connecting(struct drm_device *drm, struct drm_crtc **crtcs, uns
 		init_cnt++;
 	}

-	/* no bootloader connecting info, use the first one we found */
+	/* No bootloader connecting info: probe all connectors to find one that
+	 * already has modes.  Prefer DP/eDP over HDMI — at boot the active
+	 * display is often a USB-C DP AltMode device whose AUX/HPD fires before
+	 * HDMI is probed.  The old code only tried connectors[0] (typically
+	 * HDMI-A-1, which is disconnected), leaving connecting_head empty and
+	 * turning commit_init_connecting() into a harmless but useless no-op.
+	 * Without a proper initial modeset the display hardware pipeline is never
+	 * brought up, even though the physical DP link is fully negotiated. */
 	if (init_cnt == 0) {
-		mutex_lock(&drm->mode_config.mutex);
-		modes_count = connectors[0]->funcs->fill_modes(connectors[0], 8192, 8192);
-		/* DRM_INFO("%s found mode %d\n", __FUNCTION__, modes_count); */
-		mode = list_first_entry_or_null(&connectors[0]->modes, struct drm_display_mode, head);
-		if (mode) {
+		int j, pass;
+		struct drm_encoder *enc;
+
+		connector_ = NULL;
+		crtc_ = NULL;
+		mode = NULL;
+
+		/* pass 0: non-HDMI connectors (DP, eDP); pass 1: HDMI */
+		for (pass = 0; pass < 2 && !connector_; pass++) {
+			for (j = 0; j < connector_cnt; j++) {
+				bool is_hdmi =
+					connectors[j]->connector_type == DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_HDMIA ||
+					connectors[j]->connector_type == DRM_MODE_CONNECTOR_HDMIB;
+				if (pass == 0 && is_hdmi)
+					continue;
+				mutex_lock(&drm->mode_config.mutex);
+				modes_count = connectors[j]->funcs->fill_modes(
+						connectors[j], 8192, 8192);
+				mode = list_first_entry_or_null(
+						&connectors[j]->modes,
+						struct drm_display_mode, head);
+				mutex_unlock(&drm->mode_config.mutex);
+				if (mode) {
+					connector_ = connectors[j];
+					break;
+				}
+			}
+		}
+
+		if (mode && connector_) {
+			/* find the CRTC that can actually drive this connector */
+			drm_connector_for_each_possible_encoder(connector_, enc) {
+				for (i = 0; i < crtc_cnt; i++) {
+					if (enc->possible_crtcs & drm_crtc_mask(crtcs[i])) {
+						crtc_ = crtcs[i];
+						break;
+					}
+				}
+				if (crtc_)
+					break;
+			}
+			if (!crtc_) {
+				DRM_WARN("%s: no matching CRTC found, using crtcs[0]\n",
+					 connector_->name);
+				crtc_ = crtcs[0];
+			}
+			DRM_INFO("%s: connected at boot, using for initial modeset\n",
+				 connector_->name);
 			c = kmalloc(sizeof(*c), GFP_KERNEL | __GFP_ZERO);
-			c->crtc = crtcs[0];
-			c->connector = connectors[0];
+			c->crtc = crtc_;
+			c->connector = connector_;
 			c->mode = mode;
 			list_add_tail(&c->list, &pri->priv->connecting_head);
-			mutex_unlock(&drm->mode_config.mutex);
 		} else {
-			mutex_unlock(&drm->mode_config.mutex);
-			if (connectors[0]->funcs && connectors[0]->funcs->detect) {
-				DRM_INFO("%s Not connected, start hot-plug monitoring\n", connectors[0]->name);
-				pri->mode_monitor = sunxi_drm_create_mode_monitor(
-						connectors[0], crtcs[0], pri->priv);
-
-				if (pri->mode_monitor) {
+			/* no connector has modes — start hot-plug monitoring on
+			 * the first connector that supports detect() */
+			for (j = 0; j < connector_cnt; j++) {
+				if (connectors[j]->funcs && connectors[j]->funcs->detect) {
+					DRM_INFO("%s Not connected, start hot-plug monitoring\n",
+						 connectors[j]->name);
+					pri->mode_monitor = sunxi_drm_create_mode_monitor(
+							connectors[j], crtcs[0], pri->priv);
+				if (pri->mode_monitor)
 					sunxi_drm_start_mode_monitor(pri->mode_monitor);
-				}
-			} else {
-				DRM_INFO("%s does not support hot-swapping\n", connectors[0]->name);
+					break;
+				}
 			}
 		}
 	}
